Package: diststan
Title: Distributed Stan Fitting Across Machines with 'mirai'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Scott", "Spencer", email = "spencer.sa@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Run 'cmdstanr' MCMC chains across a small heterogeneous cluster of
    machines over SSH using 'mirai', gathering every chain's draws into one
    common directory ready for post-processing. The interface is a drop-in for
    cmdstanr's sample(): add a 'hosts' vector and let per-machine settings
    (chains, threads_per_chain, parallel_chains) be scalars or vectors aligned to
    the hosts. Each machine compiles its own native binary locally and runs one
    ordinary cmdstanr call; chain ids are distributed as global blocks so the
    pooled draws combine exactly like a single multi-chain run. A combined live
    progress board is assembled from each machine's native sampler output.
